with an uncomfortable statistic:

04:20.502 --> 04:23.871
at some point in the coming year,
one of us will probably be fired.

04:23.872 --> 04:26.364
I have no intention of it being me.

04:34.750 --> 04:35.843
I'm a bear!

04:36.151 --> 04:37.847
I'm a dancing bear!

04:38.120 --> 04:41.557
Hey, bear, bear. Bear, eat CDs!

04:43.859 --> 04:46.090
What you got, bear?
What you got? Seal?

04:46.862 --> 04:48.455
Bear eat Seal. Yeah.

04:56.272 --> 04:58.241
Bear. Bear.

04:59.008 --> 05:02.968
Bear tired. Bear tired. Oh, bear.

05:05.481 --> 05:06.748
So here's what I do.

05:06.749 --> 05:09.984
I listen to music, bands, singers, songwriters,

05:09.985 --> 05:13.254
and decide which ones have
a good chance of commercial success.

05:13.255 --> 05:16.124
I then arrange for them
to be recorded in a sympathetic manner

05:16.125 --> 05:20.128
and then we, the record company,
sell them to you, the general public.

05:20.129 --> 05:23.631
That's A&R, artiste and repertoire.

05:23.632 --> 05:24.366
Simple, eh?

05:24.367 --> 05:25.459
Get fucked.

